Responsibilities:
Perform tasks at welding station in accordance to documented processes, procedures/WI/OMS/Training/ADR.
Perform TQC as needed.
Maintain 5S and comply safety rules and regulations.
Ensure right materials are used for assembly work/process.
Account for inventory integrity by involving in cycle count as counter.
Meet welding manufacturing cycle time to ensure LEAN.
Observe and ensure quality criteria of product and raise REDLIGHT if situation warrant.
Perform other task as and when assigned by superior.
Requirements:
ITE/Diploma or higher education with working experience in Manufacturing.
With TIG welding experience of more than 1 year.
Computer literate (Internet, Email, Excel, Word, PowerPoint) an added advantage.
Must work at 2nd shift.